    <text id="B2037T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Smith refers to the unused transportation voucher of a Staunton teacher, a Miss
                    Davison.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    American Missionary Association<lb/>No. 53 John Street,
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Reverend">Rev.</abbr> R. M.
                        Manly<lb/>Richmond <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1869-02-27"><abbr expan="February">Feb.</abbr> 27th 1869</date>
                        <name type="place">New York,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Permit me to call your attention to our communication of the 12th ult, addressed
                    to you as State <abbr expan="Superintendent">Supt.</abbr> of <abbr
                        expan="Education">Ed.</abbr>, <abbr
                        expan="Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">Bu. R.F. &amp;
                        A.L.</abbr>, enclosing blanks for collecting unused <abbr
                        expan="transportation">trans<hi rend="super">n</hi></abbr> of Miss S.W.
                    Davison, a teacher at Staunton, Va., for your approval.</p>

                <p>If the blanks are now in your hands will you please refer them with the request
                    for approval to <abbr expan="General">Gen.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Orlando">O.</abbr> Brown, <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner"
                        >Ass't. Comr</abbr> &amp;c at Richmond, and oblige,</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Very Truly</salute>
                    <signed>Edw. P. Smith<lb/><abbr expan="General">Genl.</abbr> Field <abbr
                            expan="Agent">Agt.</abbr></signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">per Reeves</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
